<item>
            <title>[SOLR-3205] Better error reporting from Analysis UI</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-3205</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The new analysis UI does not behave well with invalid input.  To reproduce, from /#/singlecore/analysis&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Select a number field (int)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;put in invalid text (hello)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;click Analyse Values&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;The UI will have a red banner, but not say anything useful.  The log file will say:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;SEVERE: org.apache.solr.common.SolrException: Invalid &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;Number&lt;/span&gt;: hello
	at org.apache.solr.analysis.TrieTokenizer.reset(TrieTokenizerFactory.java:113)
	at org.apache.solr.analysis.TrieTokenizer.&amp;lt;init&amp;gt;(TrieTokenizerFactory.java:76)
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Hopefully we can get the UI to say &quot;Invalid Number: hello&quot;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
